name: Chicken momo
description: Chicken momo is a popular dish in many restaurants, especially in South Asian and Tibetan cuisine. It consists of juicy minced chicken wrapped in a thin dough, steamed, fried, or served in a spicy soup. Momo is often paired with tangy chutney or achar, enhancing its flavor

name: Buff momo
description: Buff momo is a popular Nepali dish made with minced buffalo meat, mixed with finely chopped onions, garlic, ginger, and a blend of traditional spices. The seasoned meat is wrapped in thin dough and steamed to perfection, creating juicy and flavorful dumplings. Served with a spicy tomato-based chutney.

name: Chicken chowmein
description: Chicken Chowmein is a classic and flavorful stir-fried noodle dish, popular in many restaurants. Made with thin noodles, tender chicken strips, and a mix of fresh vegetables like cabbage, carrots, and bell peppers, it's tossed in a savory soy-based sauce with aromatic spices.

name: Buff chowmein
description: Buff Chowmein is a bold and flavorful stir-fried noodle dish, made with tender buffalo meat, fresh vegetables, and aromatic spices. The noodles are tossed in a savory soy-based sauce, giving them a rich umami taste. Buffalo meat adds a unique, slightly chewy texture and deep flavor, making it a favorite among meat lovers.

name: Mix pasta
description: Mix Pasta is a delicious fusion dish that combines different types of pasta (like penne, fusilli, or spaghetti) with a rich and flavorful sauce. It includes a mix of proteins like chicken, buff,along with fresh vegetables, making it a wholesome and satisfying meal. The dish can be prepared in a creamy white sauce, a tangy tomato-based sauce, or a spicy fusion-style seasoning, catering to different taste preferences.

name: Thakali chicken khana set
description: Thakali Chicken Khana Set is a delicious and wholesome Nepali meal, known for its balanced flavors and rich taste. It features steamed rice, flavorful chicken curry, and a variety of traditional side dishes

name: Mutton sekuwa
description: Mutton Sekuwa is a flavorful and smoky Nepali grilled dish made from tender pieces of marinated mutton. The meat is seasoned with a blend of traditional spices, garlic, ginger, and mustard oil, then slow-roasted over a charcoal fire for a rich, smoky aroma.

name: Chicken üçó sekuwa
description: Chicken Sekuwa is a delicious Nepali grilled dish made from tender, marinated chicken pieces. The meat is coated with a blend of traditional spices, garlic, ginger, mustard oil, and yogurt, then grilled over charcoal for a smoky and juicy flavor.

name: Buff sukuti
description: Buff Sukuti is a traditional Nepali dried and spiced buffalo meat dish, known for its rich, smoky flavor and chewy texture. The meat is first dried and then stir-fried with onions, garlic, ginger, and Nepali spices to enhance its taste.It is typically served with beaten rice (chiura), spicy achaar, and fresh salad, making it a perfect snack or side dish

name: Sel roti
description: Sel roti is a traditional Nepali rice-based doughnut-shaped fried bread. Made from rice flour, sugar, milk, and a hint of cardamom, it has a soft and chewy interior with a crispy outer layer.
